1. Introduction

The Electric Cycle Project is designed to develop an eco-friendly and energy-efficient transportation system using electrical power. It helps reduce fuel consumption, air pollution, and transportation costs. The project combines a bicycle with an electric motor and rechargeable battery to provide smooth and comfortable travel.

2. Objective

To design an eco-friendly transportation system
To reduce fuel usage and pollution
To provide low-cost transportation
To promote green energy technology

3. Components Used

DC Motor
Rechargeable Battery
Motor Controller
Throttle
Bicycle Frame
Chain and Gear System
Wheels and Brakes
Charger

4. Working Principle

The rechargeable battery supplies power to the DC motor through the controller. When the throttle is activated, the motor rotates and drives the rear wheel of the cycle. The rider can also pedal manually when needed. The electric cycle works in both pedal mode and electric mode.

5. Advantages

Environment friendly
Low maintenance cost
Reduces fuel consumption
Easy to operate
Less physical effort
Noise-free operation

6. Applications

Daily transportation
College and office travel
Delivery services
Smart city transportation
Short-distance travel

7. Conclusion

The Electric Cycle Project is a simple, economical, and pollution-free transportation solution. It supports clean energy usage and provides efficient mobility for modern society. This project demonstrates the importance of electric vehicles in creating a sustainable future.
